The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of surgical trajectory segmentation for robot learning in robot-assisted minimally invasive surgery. This involves the use of video and kinematic data, as well as unsupervised deep learning networks and wavelet transforms. These topics are all related to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
